      "side": 0,
      "message": "It looks like I added this check in the first version of YUV2RGBEffect that supported a clamping domain. That was a much simpler domain than what is supported now using texture effect for each plane. I believe I was encountering gold image differences where it thought it could drop the clamp for the Y plane, but shouldn\u0027t for the U/V based on scale factor and how the down-sampled subset would let in U/V pixels that partially corresponded to Y pixels outside the subset.\n\nI\u0027m not sure how serious that actually was (I can\u0027t remember the image differences that prompted the check). And I wouldn\u0027t be surprised at all if all of the work in texture effect and yuv handling has mitigated this concern.\n\nI see a few changes to the bottom of the mandrill\u0027s chin in gold, but actually think that the new version of the image better matches the original scale, compared to before.",
